  "title": "Group Financial Controller (Consolidation)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Group Financial Controller (Consolidation)</strong><br /><br />We are partnering with an international organisation to appoint a Group Financial Controller with responsibility for group consolidation, financial reporting, and oversight of statutory processes across multiple entities.</p><p>This role sits within the group finance team and works closely with senior leadership, regional finance teams, and external advisors.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities.</strong></p><p>• Lead group consolidation and reporting on a regular basis in line with relevant accounting standards</p><p>• Coordinate statutory reporting and audit processes across jurisdictions, working with local teams and external auditors</p><p>• Partner with shared service or offshore teams to ensure quality, timeliness, and consistency of financial information</p><p>• Support reporting to external stakeholders, including lenders and governance bodies, where required</p><p>• Contribute to group governance, compliance, and structural matters in collaboration with senior finance leadership</p><p>• Drive enhancements to consolidation, reporting, and control frameworks as the organisation continues to evolve<br /></p><p><strong>Key Requirements</strong></p><p>• 8+ years of relevant experience in finance with proven team management</p><p>• Qualified accountant (CA, CPA, or equivalent)</p><p>• Strong experience in group consolidation and reporting within a multi entity environment</p><p>• Solid technical accounting foundation, particularly under IFRS</p><p>• Exposure to multinational or regional group structures</p><p>• Comfortable working across geographies and engaging with multiple stakeholders<br /></p><p>Singapore citizen or PR only.</p>",
